      • getTourGuideAvailableForDatesValidationIgnoreOneOffering

        public static TourGuideAvailableForDatesValidation getTourGuideAvailableForDatesValidationIgnoreOneOffering(com.vaadin.ui.DateField startDateField,
                                                                                                            int duration,
                                                                                                            DBManager dbManager,
                                                                                                            Offering ignoredOffering)
        Parameters:
        startDateField - the starting date to check
        duration - the length of the interval to check (in days)
        dbManager - A DBManager object
        ignoredOffering - the offering to ignore (can be null)
        Returns:
        whether or not the tour guide is available from time startDateField to startDateField+duration. If ignoredOffering is not null, then we ignore the time interval used by ignoredOffering when checking if tour guide is free. Useful for when editing offerings, we don't want the edited offering time-colliding with itself
